DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the planespace source code, compiled artifacts, documentation,
and any associated files distributed under this License.

"Personal Use" means use by a natural person for private, non-commercial
purposes where no monetary compensation, revenue, or organizational benefit
is derived from that use.

"Academic Research Use" means use by an individual researcher, student, or
faculty member at an accredited educational institution, solely for scholarly
research, thesis work, or coursework, provided the use is not funded by or
conducted on behalf of a commercial, governmental, or organizational entity.

"Commercial Entity" means any corporation, limited liability company,
partnership, sole proprietorship, or other for-profit legal entity.

"Non-Profit Organization" means any entity organized under a non-profit,
charitable, tax-exempt, or similar legal structure, regardless of jurisdiction,
including but not limited to 501(c) organizations, foundations, associations,
NGOs, and charities.

"Government Entity" means any agency, department, ministry, instrumentality,
or subdivision of any federal, state, provincial, municipal, or other
governmental body, whether domestic or foreign, including state-funded research
institutions and public universities acting in an institutional capacity.

"Organizational Use" means any use conducted by, for, or on behalf of a
Commercial Entity, Non-Profit Organization, or Government Entity, including
use by employees, contractors, or agents acting in that capacity.

