COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIREMENT

A separate paid commercial license is required before using the Software for
any Organizational Use. This requirement applies without exception to:

  — Commercial Entities of any size, including startups and solo operators
    operating under a registered business structure;

  — Non-Profit Organizations, including charities, foundations, open-source
    foundations, and NGOs, regardless of tax-exempt status;

  — Government Entities at any level, including publicly funded research
    laboratories and state universities acting in an institutional capacity.

The fact that an organization is non-profit, charitable, governmental, or
otherwise mission-driven does not exempt it from this requirement. The
distinction is organizational structure, not purpose or profit motive.

To obtain a commercial license, contact: licensing@planespace.dev

